			{
				"type": "Comment",
				"start": 0,
				"end": 502,
				"data": " An EMPTY <textarea> hugged by an inline <label>. The whitespace-sensitive element has no\n     content, so nothing at the label's boundary is whitespace-significant: the <label> lays out\n     block-style like any other inline element, and only the <textarea>'s own attributes react to\n     print width. Prettier instead dangles the label's closing delimiter, and the `</label` suffix\n     it adds to the textarea line is what pushes the attributes over — see\n     prettier_variant_label_dangle. "
			},
			{
				"type": "Text",
				"start": 502,
				"end": 504,
				"raw": "\n\n",
				"data": "\n\n"
			},
